==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''calyx'' from {{Gr.}} ''kalyx''
===Noun===
'''calyx''' (''pl.'' calyces)

#(''botany'') Collective term for the [[sepal]]s of a [[flower]], ''i.e.'' the outermost whorl of flower parts, when this is not the same in appearance as the next such whorl (the [[corolla]]).
#A [[cup]]-like [[structure]] in the [[kidney]]
